@{fg background}@{bg text} Project Directory @{fg text}@{bg background}

All files relating to a specific project, such as simulation scripts
and schematic sheets, are maintained in a Project Directory.  A
Project Directory may contain a single design, or multiple designs that
are part of a large partitioned project.  While any number of Project
Directories may be created, only one can be active at a time.  

@{fg background}@{bg text} Project Manager @{fg text}@{bg background}

The @{" Project Manager " LINK Picture_Database/pmanager.0/MAIN} program is used to create or select the current 
active Project Directory.  Since many of the Electrics programs learn
of the active Project Directory upon startup, the selection process must
be done before they are run.

To select a Project Directory, begin by running the Project Manager 
program.  A file requester will appear, listing only Volumes and
Directories.  Select an existing Directory name to become the active
Project Directory, or enter the name of a new one to be created.
Click on the "Ok" button accept the selection, or "Cancel" to not
continue.

@{fg background}@{bg text} Project Directory Preparation @{fg text}@{bg background}

After a Project Directory has been selected, the Project Manager will
then create a number of sub-directories inside the Project Directory.
If any of the sub-directories already exist, they will not be touched.

Most of the sub-directories are for private use.  However, the
"Scripts" sub-directory will be of interest, as it is where the
project simulation scripts are kept.

The Project Directory is now ready for use.
@ENDNODE
